,Recommended,212050,8357858,"Posted: 27 December, 2013",all,linuvian,"This has been sitting in my games library for about 6 months. I finally got around to playing it and ended up finishing it in one sitting (It's pretty long, so that's meant as a testament toward quality, not a comment about length).Very nice game. I found the story intriguing and the atmosphere was great, particularly at certain points (one chase scene had me jumping and panicking more than most of the horror games I've played). The mechanics were nice as well. The four-playable-characters aspect was neat and I loved being able to instantly change between them (though trying to remember who was carrying what was sometimes annoying). I liked the implementation of Long and Short-term memory, and thus the ability to use things that you can't physically pick up as conversation prompts. There was some good humor mixed in, which I always appreciate in my point-n-clicks, and the art was lovely throughout.I did encounter a couple bugs along the way, but nothing too big, and nothing that I couldn't fix by loading (though if you didn't save a lot as I do they might have been more of a problem). My main gripe about the game is that some of the puzzles are VERY overly complicated. Don't get me wrong, I like difficult puzzles, but I do NOT like tedious puzzles and leaps of logic, and unfortunately Resonance has its fair share of those. I'm willing to look past them, though, because not all of the puzzles were that way, and because I liked the story and characters so much.All in all, it's a game I really enjoyed and will play again someday. Reccommend it to any adventure game fan, especially on sale."
