,Recommended,212050,414032,"Posted: 21 February, 2013",all,Seventh Arrow,"Resonance is a fantastic game. Although the mechanics will not be anything new or different to anyone who's played 90's adventure games, the story and character interactions are great. Also, if your background with adventure games involves comical, colourful fare like Monkey Island and Day of the Tentacle, you may find the dark, sometimes bleak setting of Resonance to be an interesting twist.For me, having a retro adventure game set in a story where the characters face conspiracies, betrayals, and the threat of atomic annihilation was pretty compelling. True, there is a fair share of pixel hunting and the occasional stumper of a puzzle, but overall the flow of gameplay is quite smooth. Don't read any spoilers if you're interested in this game at all! It will be worth it."
76561197970491083,Recommended,212050,415818,"Posted: 19 August, 2012",all,En4cer,"This is a great game. It has an excellent story, challenging puzzles, decent voice acting and catchy music. The trickiest part of the game is the Short Term Memory (STM) feature. It involves dragging things from the environment, such as a locked door, and putting them in the STM list. You can talk to an NPC and ask them about that locked door by selecting it from the STM list. Overall, you will enjoy this nice little indie game."
