76561198072243965,Recommended,212050,7954258,"Posted: 7 December, 2013",all,Wekken,"I'm definitely a fan of the point-and-click adventure, so in that way this may be a tad biased, but I certainly enjoyed this game. A good plot (as long as you don't overthink it!) with some puzzles that get you thinking, but not enough to bring you out in a cold sweat for the most part. It seems that some of the harder problems can be dodged so that you can continue if things just get too much at those points...but where's the fun in that? :-)I've played Gemini Rue from Wadjet Eye as well, and though the story genre and mood are quite different, this is of a similar quality in my opinion...maybe a little better."
