76561198036314516,Recommended,212050,13202463,"Posted: 2 December, 2014",all,Kurt Danger,"I picked this game up for ~£2 on sale and, when i first booted it up and played for a bit, I wasn't too impressed...but the more I played, the more I enjoyed it.The point and click interaction feels a bit clunky at first (especially the Long Term Memory / Short Term Memory interaction), but after a while it becomes second nature and I began to appreciate it much more.The story  & characters are what really sells this game in the grand scheme of things. The story is very good and does a good job of engrossing you in the world. The charaters are also very well done, leaving you wanting to find out more about them & hearing more about what they have to say.A lot of the puzzle solving elements in this game really don't hold your hand. Assuming you don't use a walkthrough, they may take a while to solve if you haven't picked up the appropriate item along the way.... so you may end up having to re-visit earlier locations to find something that you previously missed.The graphics, although I'm assuming they were meant to look like a really old  retro point n' click game, do take a bit of getting used to though.Thoroughly enjoyed this one. If you liked / like the look of this, i'd also reccommed picking up Gemini Rue, which is also awesome."
